¡Muchas gracias a todos los implicados! ❤️#PeopleinRed2025

We share with you a summary of the @peopleinredgala , the solidarity event promoted by @fundaciolluita that we sponsored for the fifth consecutive year, true to our commitment to scientific research.

Many thanks to everyone involved! ❤️ #PeopleinRed2025

El pasado 25 de abril celebramos en Barcelona la segunda edición de “connectoMe: 4D approach to aesthetic indications”, un evento único donde profesionales médicos de todo el mundo se reunieron para una jornada formativa única. 

Durante el evento presentamos nuestra filosofía terapéutica PATH: un enfoque integral que combina tratamientos sinérgicos para resultados personalizados más efectivos. Con la participación de médicos expertos como la dra. @drabeatrizbeltran , el dr. @drsilik , @drdefelipe y el dr. Javier Beut @instituto_dr_beut exploramos las técnicas y protocolos más avanzados y dimos a conocer mesofiller®️ nexha y el concepto revolucionario de la neoestimulación. 

¡Gracias a todos los que nos acompañaron!

Mi fotoprotección 360º sin complicaciones de @mesoestetic

Completo mi defensa con mesoprotech PLE gummies, fotoprotección oral con antioxidantes y activos que refuerzan la piel desde el interior.

Práctico, completo y eficaz.

A full circle moment… in the heart of Times Square 💫

10 years ago, almost to the day, Shhh Silk was born out of a family trip to New York. I wandered these same streets dreaming of what could be… never imagining that one day, a vision sparked in a hotel room would light up a billboard in Times Square.

Today, that dream became real.

Seeing our brand, our message, on one of the most iconic stages in the world has brought tears to my eyes and pride to my heart.

“In a world that never stops, remember to pause.”

This has always been more than silk to me. It’s a reminder to soften, to rest, to reconnect with self. And to now share that message with millions in a city that never sleeps? Divine timing.

To our customers, our team, our partners, our believers, you’ve helped shape this moment. Thank you for every order, every word of encouragement, every pause you’ve taken with us.

This is for the dreamers, the doers, and anyone who ever wondered if a vision from a hotel room in New York could one day light up the city itself.

We’re just getting started.

With so much love and gratitude,
Olivia x
Founder, Shhh Silk

At Shhh Silk, every detail is intentionally designed to elevate your rest.​​​​​​​​
​​​​​​​​
From the softness of our 100% pure mulberry silk to the hidden YKK Japanese zippers in our pillowcases, every feature has a functional purpose, not just beauty, but true betterment for your sleep and self-care rituals.​​​​​​​​
​​​​​​​​
Why hidden zippers? They’re crafted to stay discreet and secure, keeping your pillow perfectly in place all night long, while maintaining a seamless, luxurious feel. We’ve been using hidden zippers for 10 years, we were the first silk pillowcase in the world to innovate with our hidden zippers so that they would stay on your pillow all night. ​​​​​​​​
​​​​​​​​
Because you deserve products that are thoughtfully made, beautifully designed, and purposefully aligned with the art of rest.​​​​​​​​

Design Fact: YKK stands for Yoshida Kōgyō Kabushiki gaisha (吉田工業株式会社), which translates to Yoshida Manufacturing Corporation. The company was founded in Tokyo, Japan, in 1934 and is now the largest zipper manufacturer in the world. 
​​​​​​​​

Bhawanipore, East Bengal joint-winners of First Division Championship

Bhawanipore Club and East Bengal Club were announced joint winners after the First Division Championship final match ended in a draw on the fifth and final day at the Eden Gardens on Thursday. 

Vivek Singh was awarded the player of the match. 

In the summit clash, batting first, Bhawanipore Club scored a mammoth 643/6 decl in 170 overs in their first innings. 

Shakir Habib Gandhi (220), Vivek (176 not out), Abhishek Raman (93) were the star performers with the bat. 

In reply, East Bengal, in their first innings, were 243/8 in 106.4 overs, when heavy rain stopped play. 

With the weather showing no signs of improvement and as both the team’s first innings were not completed, the match was drawn and Bhawanipore & East Bengal were announced joint winners. 

For East Bengal, Satyaki Dutta (53), Kanishk Seth (48 not out) were the pick of the batters.

For Bhawanipore, Ravi Kumar bagged 3 for 60 while Anubhav Tyagi claimed 2 for 38.

#CAB

First Div Final: East Bengal 147/4 on Day 4 in reply to Bhawanipore’s 643/6

Bhawanipore Club scored a mammoth 643/6 decl in 170 overs in their first innings against East Bengal Club in the First Division Championship final at the Eden Gardens on Wednesday. 

Shakir Habib Gandhi (220), Vivek Singh (176 not out), Abhishek Raman (93), Arindam Ghosh (57) and Pradipta Pramanik (48) were the star performers with the bat. 

For East Bengal, Suraj Sindhu Jaiswal and Vikas Singh bagged 2 wickets each while Writtick Chatterjee and Kanisk Seth claimed one each.

In reply, East Bengal, in their first innings, were 147/4 in 70 overs at stumps on the fourth and penultimate day.

Satyaki Dutta (53), Akash Ghatak (32) were the pick of the batters.

At stumps, Writtick (12) and Ayan Bhattacharya (12) remained unbeaten. 

For Bhawanipore, Rajkumar Pal, Ravi Kumar, Anubhav Tyagi and Jayojit Basu bagged a wicket each.

Creamy Lemon Parsley Pasta
Serves 4
About $2.50 per person. 

Ingredients
1/2 yellow onion, sliced 
2 cloves garlic, whole
1 Tbsp olive oil
1/2 lemon, juiced
15 oz cooked chick peas, drained
1 tsp rosemary
2 Tbsp grated vegan parmesan
2 vegan chicken bullion cubes 
A few sprigs of fresh parsley, torn
1 lb pasta of choice
Water
Salt snd pepper 

Directions:
Cook pasta in a large pot according to pavkage directions (reserve 1/2 cup pasta water before draining)

In a frying pan on medium heat: 

Add oil, onion, garlic, rosemary, salt and pepper. Cook for 5 minutes. 

Add beans and enough water to barely cover the mixture. 

Add bulllion cubes and stir. 

Add the fresh lemon juice, stir, and cover the pan. Simmer, covered, for 15 minutes then pour into a blender. Add a handful of the fresh parsley and blend until smooth. Then return the blended bean mixture to the frying pan.

Add parmesan, pasta water, stir, and then fold the pasta into the bean sauce to coat. 

Rip a few parsley leaves on top, add a touch more olive oil If you want and enjoy!  If you love the texture of mac and cheese, youll love this recipe.
